# 8. Environment Governance Strategy

## Environment Structure

| Environment | Purpose                              |
| ----------- | ------------------------------------ |
| Development | Active development and configuration |
| Test/UAT    | Validation and testing               |
| Production  | Controlled business operations       |

---

## Environment Governance Rules

* No unmanaged customizations in Production
* All deployments must occur through solutions
* All flows must be solution-aware
* Environment variables required for configurable settings
* Connection references required for integrations
* Source control mandatory for enterprise solutions
* Production access restricted to authorized personnel

---

# 9. ALM Governance Standards

## Application Lifecycle Management Standards

### Source Control

* All enterprise solutions stored in source control
* Branching strategy required
* Pull request reviews required

### Deployment Standards

* All deployments must pass UAT approval
* Rollback strategy required for production releases
* Solution versioning standards required
* Release notes mandatory

### Solution Standards

* Managed solutions for Production
* Unmanaged solutions for Development only
* Solution segmentation encouraged
* Publisher and naming standards enforced

---

# 10. Development Standards

## Naming Standards

### Examples

| Component Type | Naming Example        |
| -------------- | --------------------- |
| Solution       | META_SalesCore        |
| Flow           | META_AccountSync_Flow |
| Plugin         | META.Account.Plugin   |
| JavaScript     | meta_accountForm.js   |
| Table          | meta_accountterritory |

---

## Plugin Standards

* Tracing required
* Structured exception handling required
* Async processing preferred when applicable
* Secure/unsecure configuration usage encouraged
* Plugin step documentation required

---

## Power Automate Standards

* Service account usage for enterprise flows
* Retry policies required for integrations
* Child flows encouraged for reusable logic
* Naming standards enforced
* Ownership documentation required

---

## JavaScript Standards

* Namespace pattern required
* Async patterns encouraged
* Form event documentation required
* Minimize unsupported DOM manipulation

---

